<html>

<body metal:use-macro="here/prefs_main_template/macros/master">

<metal:block fill-slot="top_slot"
             tal:define="dummy python:request.set('disable_border',1)" />

<div metal:fill-slot="prefs_configlet_main">

<tal:comment replace="nothing">
    <div class="portalMessage" tal:content="structure python: view.context.request.form" />
</tal:comment>

<h1>Edit CSS</h1>

    <a href=""
       class="link-parent"
       tal:attributes="href string:$portal_url/plone_control_panel"
       i18n:translate="label_up_to_plone_setup">
        Up to Site Setup
    </a>


    <form method="post" action="@@edit_css">

        <p>This is where you can put CSS to override Plone's default CSS.
        <span class="discreet">Don't forget to turn on CSS debug mode first. You can do that easily from within Plone by installing this <a href="http://plone.org/products/collective.controlpanel.debug_css">add-on</a>.</p>

        <div class="field">

        <fieldset>
            <legend>Edit CSS</legend>

            <textarea rows="25" name="edit_css" tal:content="view/getPloneCustom"></textarea>

            <div class="formControls" style="padding-top: 1em">
                <input class="context"
                     type="submit"
                     name="submit"
                     value="Save" />
            </div>
        </fieldset>

        </div>

    </form>


</div>

</body>

</html>
